      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I was just using the goblins as a metaphor to illustrate the idea of holding funds until certain conditions are met. Think of it like a treasure chest, where the funds are locked away until the transaction is complete. Now, let's get to the actual process.\n\nWhen you set up an escrow account, the lender will typically hold a portion of the purchase price in the escrow account until the closing date. This is usually done through an automated transfer from your bank account to the escrow account.\n\nOn the closing date, the escrow agent will disburse the funds to the seller, minus any outstanding fees or charges. The funds are then released from the escrow account, and the transaction is complete. It's like the goblins have been paid off, and the treasure chest is now empty.\n\nThe escrow process typically involves the following steps:\n\n1. The lender holds a portion of the purchase price in the escrow account.\n2. The escrow agent disburses funds to the seller on the closing date.\n3. The funds are released from the escrow account, and the transaction is complete.\n\nIt's a bit like a game of musical chairs, where the funds are held until the right moment to be released. And just",
